data.title: TECHTRON® PPS
data.meta_description: Explore our Techtron PPS offerings at Total Plastics. Discover how Techtron PPS's superior chemical resistance and low moisture absorption can enhance your operations.
data.text:
Explore Techtron® PPS: Unmatched in Chemical Resistance

Dive into the realm of advanced engineering plastics with Total Plastics' Techtron® PPS. Known for its broad chemical resistance, this polyphenylene sulfide product stands out in challenging environments, resisting solvents up to 392°F and displaying inertness to steam, strong bases, fuels, and acids.

Key Features of Techtron® PPS

Outstanding chemical resistance for challenging applications

High thermal stability, withstanding harsh temperatures

Excellent mechanical strength ensuring durability

Low moisture absorption for reliable performance

Good electrical properties for versatile usage

Meets rigorous industry standards for safety and quality

Technical Specifications

Material: PPS (Polyphenylene Sulfide)

Maximum Temperature Resistance: 392°F (200°C)

Applications of Techtron® PPS

The superior chemical resistance and mechanical properties of Techtron® PPS open doors to a myriad of applications. It's an excellent choice for industries such as chemical processing, aerospace, electrical, and more.

Why Choose Total Plastics?

At Total Plastics, quality and customer satisfaction are our priority. Choosing Techtron® PPS means you're investing in a product backed by years of industry expertise and a commitment to excellence. Our team is here to provide high-quality, reliable solutions for your project needs.
